President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Heath P. Tarbert to the Department of the Treasury. Tarbert, a leading attorney in the financial services field with over 15 years of experience, will serve as Assistant Secretary of the Treasury, International Markets and Development if confirmed. He is currently a partner at the global law firm Allen & Overy LLP and has previously worked in all three branches of the Federal Government, including as Special Counsel to the Senate Banking Committee, Associate Counsel to President George W. Bush, and law clerk to U.S. Supreme Court Justice Clarence Thomas. Tarbert's policy work includes being a Senior Fellow at the Harvard Law School Program on International Financial Systems. He is also a Certified Public Accountant and a Chartered Financial Analyst charterholder. Tarbert holds a BS from Mount St. Mary's University, a JD and SJD from the University of Pennsylvania, and a DPhil from Oxford University where he was a Thouron Scholar.